<br>
Get a clean large garbage bag, fold the comforter up nicely and put it inside the bag and try and get it as air tight as possible.  Leave it in there for 24 hours and it will be fine.  <br>
<br>
As for your pillows and other bedding - all you have to do is wash anything that can be washed (i.e. pillow cases, sheets and blankets) and put the pillows in another bag and let them sit for 24 hours as well.<br>
<br>
I know it's a pain in the ass but it's better that worrying about lice.  (make sure you wash your brushes if you think she may have used them - put them in a container with baking soda and really hot water and let sit a couple of hours).<br>
<br>
